{"id":84880,"link":"https://chinadigitaltimes.net/chinese/2010/07/译者：图集：2010国际环保摄影奖获奖作品选/","date":"2010-07-14T21:03:11Z","modified":"2010-09-23T22:07:01Z","title":"译者：图集：2010国际环保摄影奖获奖作品选","content":"<p>原作者：<br />\n来源<a href=\"http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/07/100712-international-conservation-photography-awards-pictures/#conservation-photography-award-2010-macaques_23247_600x450.jpg\">Photos: 2010 International Conservation Photography Awards</a><br />\n译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/95021\">WideBridge</a><br />\n<img title=\"Photo: A family of Japanese macaques relaxes together in a thermal spring \" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-macaques_23247_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: A family of Japanese macaques relaxes together in a thermal spring \" width=\"600\" height=\"396\" /></p>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN-US\"> 1. </span><span>温泉池里的猕猴</span><span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></p>\n<p>摄影：奥克萨纳·珀金斯<span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p>在长野<span lang=\"EN-US\">Yaenkoen</span>公园，猕猴一家过着惬意的生活，不仅得到保护还能像人类一样享受温泉。此照片获得2010国际环保摄影赛野生动物类一等奖，该全球性的摄影大赛旨在激发世人对环境保护的意识。国际环保摄影奖评委、平面设计师辛西娅·霍尔评价道：“这张照片完美地展现了猕猴一家互相关爱的生活场面。猕猴父亲歪着脑袋，一副陶醉的样子，小猕猴用小手触摸父亲，而猕猴母亲则流露出满怀深情，这一瞬间立刻就会让人喜欢上。”<span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></p>\n<p><img title=\"Photo: People pick through refuse at a dump in India while storks perched on the pile wait their turn. \" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-storks-garbage_23254_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: People pick through refuse at a dump in India while storks perched on the pile wait their turn. \" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></p>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN\"> 2. </span></span><span>古瓦哈蒂垃圾场</span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p>摄影：桑德什·科杜尔</span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p>大秃鹳属于濒危物种，却成为印度古瓦哈蒂垃圾场的常客，不过，它们必须耐心地站在以捡拾垃圾为生的人群后面，等他们离去才能上阵觅食。霍尔评价说：“在照片前景的位置，模糊的人头攒动，与此同时，大秃鹳站立在垃圾堆上等待机会，希望能见缝插针捞到残羹剩饭。作者定格的这一瞬间，人在控制场面，动物只有耐心等待的份。这张照片堪称一流，从色彩到构图都非常完美。<span lang=\"EN-US\">”</span>它获得今年</span><span>国际环保摄影大赛</span><span>风险类头等</span><span>奖</span><span>。</span><span lang=\"EN\"><img title=\"Photo: Sunbeams shine through fog and mist in a snow-covered pine forest\" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-pines_23248_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: Sunbeams shine through fog and mist in a snow-covered pine forest\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></span></h2>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN\"> 3. </span></span><span>松林中的晨光</span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p>摄影：伊森</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">•</span><span>韦尔蒂</span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p>清晨伊森</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">•</span><span>威尔</span><span>蒂</span><span>迎着朝阳登上巴林山，当第一缕阳光穿过雾霭照进华盛顿贝克</span><span>夸尔米</span><span>国家森林的时候，他用镜头捕捉了这一瞬间。这张照片让威尔</span><span>蒂荣</span><span>获了</span><span>环保摄影大赛</span><span>学生类最高荣誉。他自己写道：“这样的美景仅持续了几秒钟，幸运的是，我立刻用相机拍纪录了下来。”</span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p><img title=\"Photo: A seal sits among the abandoned equipment and buildings of an old Antarctic whaling station\" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-seal_23253_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: A seal sits among the abandoned equipment and buildings of an old Antarctic whaling station\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></h2>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN\"> 4. </span>坐在</span><span>推进器上的海狗</span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p>摄影：苏珊尼</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">•</span><span>维森贝格</span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p>南极斯特罗姆内斯湾的这座废弃捕鲸站曾经收留了英国探险家欧内斯特·沙克尔顿，充满传奇色彩的他有过一段生死历程，它的最后阶段就是在此处度过的。对于那些被追杀到此地的鲸来说，这里显得不那么友善，可以说这里让它们濒临灭绝。前来迎接到访摄影师</span><span>苏珊尼</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">•</span><span>维森贝格</span><span>的只有一只雄性<span><span>海豹</span></span>，但这张照片却让摄影师荣获</span><span>环保摄影大赛</span><span>危机类奖。栖息在一片废弃物中的<span><span>海豹不禁让</span></span>维森伯格纳闷：“这一切它能明白吗？”<span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span></p>\n<p><img title=\"Photo: Evening light cloaks the rumpled landscape of Death Valley's badlands\" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-sandstorm_23251_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: Evening light cloaks the rumpled landscape of Death Valley's badlands\" width=\"494\" height=\"450\" /></h2>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN\"> 5. </span>死亡谷荒原</span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span></p>\n<p>摄影：</span><span>特里希·惠丝</span></p>\n<p>傍晚的太阳在死亡谷凹凸不平的地形上投下柔和的光亮，这里是地球上最炎热、最干燥、海拔最低而且最不适合人居的地方。此处有记录的最高气温是<span lang=\"EN-US\">57</span>摄氏度，年均降水量不到<span lang=\"EN-US\">5</span>厘米。一场过往的沙尘暴为摄影师特里希·惠丝布置这个完美的场景，她作品荣获摄影大赛地貌类一等奖。她的另一幅作品“扎布里斯基之角”则纪录了另一个自然奇观<span lang=\"EN-US\"> &#8212; </span>侵蚀的力量。自然风化造就了荒原错综复杂的模样，也吸引了众人的视线。</span></p>\n<p><img title=\"Photo: The big bell of a pale sea nettle seems to glow with translucent light \" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-sea-nettle_23252_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: The big bell of a pale sea nettle seems to glow with translucent light \" width=\"600\" height=\"396\" /></h2>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN\"> 6. </span></span><span>半透明刺水母</span></p>\n<p>摄影：</span><span>吉姆·帕特森</span></p>\n<p>这张照片摄于</span><span>美国加利福尼亚州蒙特利市圣卡洛斯海滩附近，明亮而半透明的刺水母帮助吉姆·帕特森一举夺得摄影大赛水下类作品一等奖。这种水母看上去非常美丽，但却能给对手以致命一击。被水母毒须蛰到后会疼痛难已，成群漂浮的水母常常令游泳者苦恼不已。水母会用自己的触须麻痹小动物，然后把对方当成美餐。</span></p>\n<p><img title=\"Photo: Tufts of windblown grass cling to life on giant desert sand dunes\" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-grass-dunes_23246_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: Tufts of windblown grass cling to life on giant desert sand dunes\" width=\"600\" height=\"399\" /></h2>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN\"> 7. </span></span><span>挣扎求生的野草</span></p>\n<p>摄影：菲利普·莫斯</span></p>\n<p>位于西南非洲的纳米布沙漠是世界上面积最大、历史最悠久的沙漠，它已经存在<span lang=\"EN-US\">5500</span>万年。纳米布沙漠有无数座沙丘，高度接近<span lang=\"EN-US\">300</span>米，时常随季风漂移，沙漠中的<span lang=\"EN-US\">Astenatherum</span>草也因此在恶劣环境下挣扎着求生。尽管如此，却有<span lang=\"EN-US\">3500</span>种植物幸存下来，其中有一半在地球的其他地方无法生长。</span></h2>\n<p><img title=\"Photo: A shot under a Lake Washington bridge shows untreated rainwater falling from a pipe into the lake below \" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-puget_23249_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: A shot under a Lake Washington bridge shows untreated rainwater falling from a pipe into the lake below \" width=\"600\" height=\"437\" /></p>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN\">8. </span></span><span>华盛顿湖桥畔</span></p>\n<p>摄影：汤姆·瑞斯</span></p>\n<p>总部在西雅图的国际环保摄影奖</span><span>还设有</span><span>帕吉特桑德</span><span>风险类奖，以便让本地摄影师关注自己身边环境的生态状况。在这张照片中，未经处理的雨水携带汽车排放的污染物流入桥下的华盛顿湖，污染了鲑鱼的栖息地。霍尔表示，评委们觉得让这张照片获一等奖有助于推动环境问题的解决。她说：“这张照片有让你要被这些脏水从头淋到脚的感觉”。</span></p>\n<p><img title=\"Photo: Three sailfish hunt sardines, and one has stabbed a sardine with its spear\" src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/232/cache/conservation-photography-award-2010-sailfish_23250_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: Three sailfish hunt sardines, and one has stabbed a sardine with its spear\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></p>\n<p>图<span lang=\"EN\"> 9.</span></span><span lang=\"EN\"> </span><span>旗鱼出击</span></p>\n<p>摄影：斯图亚特·</span><span>韦斯特莫兰德</span></p>\n<p>这是在距墨西哥尤卡坦半岛穆赫雷斯岛<span lang=\"EN-US\">16</span>公里的大海深处，一群旗鱼正在对沙丁鱼实施“围剿”。旗鱼是海上游动速度最快的鱼类，每小时可达<span lang=\"EN-US\">110</span>公里。它们凭借自己的速度和宽大的脊鳍用矛状尖嘴刺杀猎物，这个稍纵即逝的瞬间正好被摄影师</span><span>斯图亚特·</span><span>韦斯特莫兰德捕捉到。这张照片夺得以大赛创始人命名的“沃尔夫艺术奖”。</span></h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/117560#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p>\n<p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/92797/117476?from=rss_related\">停止动物战争</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/156174/117535?from=rss_related\">关于海地灾后6个月的报告</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/74670/117328?from=rss_related\">福特开发出新技术，将豆油运用于汽车生产</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/bianbin/117182?from=rss_related\">【绘画图集】伦敦交通博物馆的自行车绘画大赛作品</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/117186?from=rss_related\">2010夏季：被石油惊醒的恶梦</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/391336618/yeeyan/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/117560\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"0\" height=\"0\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan/391336618/art01.html\"><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan/391336618/art01.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>\n<p>请看原文：<br />\n<a title=\"图集：2010国际环保摄影奖获奖作品选\" href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/117560\" target=\"_blank\">图集：2010国际环保摄影奖获奖作品选</a></p>\n","author":176,"categories":[20534],"tags":[12976,10099,9151,9014,8840]}